After a bit of playing around with some aircraft designs on kerbin, i decided to make use of them! Haven't been any further than duna before, an that was with a tiny little probe.

So up we go!

Intersect and aerobrake in Jool.

Intersect and aerobrake in Laythe.

Put craft into very low stable orbit and detach one of the planes, use a tiny thruster to deorbit.

Find a good spot and land. Then repeat process for second plane, with a different landing spot nearby.

The transit stage was dropped and destroyed.

MISSION SUCCESS! Both planes landed without damage and plenty of fuel left to explore!

Very happy man!
float planes,brillance! Care to share .craft on them?

Nice planes. What are you using for floats? I've had pretty good luck with the pontoons in Firespitter but I've never seen your floats before. Do you also have one of the mods that changes how water behaves (Boat Parts of Hooligan Submarine?).

The floats are just stock structural fuselage parts, unmodified water physics too.

The trick to a soft enough landing and take off is the 3rd engine thrusting down through the COM, let's you slow the plane down to <20m/s needed for landing, and thrust to lift the nose out of the water. It doesn't have enough power to actually vtol i don't think though. You can see the glow from the engine below:
